<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="420" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,538,2041]" pageId="1" pageNumber="420">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,487,718,745]" pageId="1" pageNumber="420">
Description of 
<typeStatus box="[377,482,719,745]" pageId="1" pageNumber="420">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
TL = 
<quantity box="[560,664,719,745]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.41" pageId="1" pageNumber="420" unit="mm" value="14.1">14.1 mm</quantity>
; TL-H = 
<quantity box="[771,875,718,745]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" pageId="1" pageNumber="420" unit="mm" value="13.5">13.5 mm</quantity>
; MW = 
<quantity box="[971,1061,718,745]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="420" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
. Body oval, elongate, slightly attenuated posteriorly, dorsoventrally depressed; subparallel medially, widest just behind middle, lateral outline continuous in dorsal aspect.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,538,2041]" pageId="1" pageNumber="420">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,288,826,853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="420">Colour.</emphasis>
Dorsal surface predominantly black. Head capsule black with clypeus and frons slightly testaceous (
<figureCitation box="[160,240,863,889]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[278,1310,179,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[278,1310,179,1918]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of H. hauthi sp. nov., holotype, male (a); H. lateralis (b) and H. panguana (c), both from Panguana Research Station, Huanuco Department, Peru. Scale bar = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3688348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3688348/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="420">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
). Pronotum black with lateral margins testaceous. Elytron black, lateral margin of apex sparsely irrorated. Ventral surface predominantly black, antenna, prosternum, mouthparts and fore legs testaceous, middle and hind legs almost black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,538,2041]" pageId="1" pageNumber="420">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,492,970,997]" pageId="1" pageNumber="420">Structure and sculpture.</emphasis>
Head with fine dense punctation and scattered stronger punctures; additionally with strong punctures concentrated in two spots in anterior third, and with longitudinal rows of strong punctures along postero-medial margins of eyes. Pronotum with posterolateral angle produced and acute, posterior margin broadly sinuate and recurved lateral to basomedial lobe. Pronotum with fine, dense punctation, and row of strong punctures along anterior margin; scattered strong punctures and traces of wrinkles near lateral margins, and row of stronger punctures near posterior margin on both sides of middle. Elytron with very fine microreticulation and scattered stronger punctures. Two rows of well-developed and deep punctures visible. Ventral surface with fine microreticulation; metacoxae and ventrites with fine scattered punctation and with stronger punctures along margin of last ventrite. Prosternal process almost flat. Metaventral wing relatively broad medially, narrow laterally with anterolateral margin straight. Dorsal surface of protarsomeres I and II with strong and dense reticulations and a series of spines. Protibia with stout pegs on apicodorsal surface. Mesotarsomeres ventrally with a small basal brush of setae. Posterior surface of metafemur with few large punctures on anterior surface and without interspersed small punctures. Metatibia without punctures on anterior surface; posterior surface with dorsal series of seven bifid setae curved ventro-basally, not parallel to dorsal margin; metatibial spurs acuminate apically. Metatarsal claws unequal, anterior claw shorter than posterior one.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,538,2041]" pageId="1" pageNumber="420">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,378,1510,1537]" pageId="1" pageNumber="420">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Median lobe of aedeagus narrow in ventral view; in lateral view enlarged in apical third and with apex rounded (
<figureCitation box="[375,445,1547,1573]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–3" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1939,1964]" captionTargetBox="[185,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[185,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 2–3. Median lobe of aedeagus in dorsal (a) and lateral view (b): H. hauthi sp. nov. (2), H. lateralis (3) and H. panguana (4). The anterior margin of the membranous lateral “wings” of the median lobe in 3b and 4 b have been enhanced digitally for more contrast and better visibility. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3688350" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3688350/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="420">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Parameres are not illustrated because by no means useful in identification of most species of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Megna et al. 2019)" baseAuthorityName="Megna" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[232,578,1583,1609]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hydaticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[232,346,1583,1609]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="420">Hydaticus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Megna, Y. S. &amp; Balke, M. &amp; Apenborn, R. &amp; Hendrich, L." box="[360,571,1583,1609]" pageId="1" pageNumber="420" pagination="113 - 130" refId="ref3615" refString="Megna, Y. S., Balke, M., Apenborn, R. &amp; Hendrich, L. (2019) A review of Peruvian diving beetles of the genus Hydaticus Leach, 1817, with description of Hydaticus (Prodaticus) panguana sp. nov. and notes on other Neotropical species (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae). Zootaxa, 4615 (1), 113 - 130. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4615.1.5" type="journal article" year="2019">
Megna 
<emphasis box="[447,503,1583,1609]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="420">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,538,2041]" pageId="1" pageNumber="420">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,440,1618,1645]" pageId="1" pageNumber="420">Sexual dimorphism.</emphasis>
Male with protarsomeres I-III enlarged to form a large oval palette ventrally bearing 22 rounded suckers of different sizes; male protarsomeres I and II with a series of spines across dorsal surface; mesotarsomeres I–III moderately enlarged, ventrally with 14 rounded suckers. Wrinkles on pronotum similar to those in males. Female with TL = 
<quantity box="[436,538,1727,1753]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3599999999999999" pageId="1" pageNumber="420" unit="mm" value="13.6">13.6 mm</quantity>
; TL-H = 
<quantity box="[641,743,1727,1753]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.29" pageId="1" pageNumber="420" unit="mm" value="12.9">12.9 mm</quantity>
; MW = 
<quantity box="[833,921,1727,1753]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.4" pageId="1" pageNumber="420" unit="mm" value="7.4">7.4 mm</quantity>
; metatarsomeres of female with natatory setae on posteroventral margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="420" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,538,2041]" pageId="1" pageNumber="420">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,462,1798,1825]" pageId="1" pageNumber="420">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
The habitus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hendrich &amp; Balke, 2020" authorityName="Hendrich &amp; Balke" authorityYear="2020" box="[636,829,1799,1825]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hydaticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hauthi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[636,829,1799,1825]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="420">Hydaticus hauthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,925,1799,1825]" pageId="1" pageNumber="420">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[835,925,1799,1825]" pageId="1" pageNumber="420" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is near to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Megna, Balke, Apenborn &amp; Hendrich, 2019" authorityName="Megna, Balke, Apenborn &amp; Hendrich" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hydaticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panguana">
<emphasis box="[1119,1265,1800,1825]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="420">H. panguana</emphasis>
